3. Student Database

Create a Students table containing:

- Student ID
- Name
- Class
- Section
- Barcode Number
- Phone Number
- Photo Path

Create an Attendance table containing:

- Attendance ID
- Student ID
- Date
- Time
- Status (Present/Late)

4. Dashboard

Create a modern dark-themed dashboard with:

- Total Students
- Present Today
- Absent Today
- Late Students
- Attendance Percentage

Buttons:

- Scan Barcode
- Add Student
- View Students
- View Attendance
- Reports
- Exit

5. Add Student Module

Allow users to:

- Enter student details
- Upload student photo
- Generate barcode automatically
- Save data into SQLite database

6. Barcode Scanner Module

Support:

- Webcam barcode scanning using OpenCV and Pyzbar
- USB barcode scanner input

When barcode is detected:

- Search student in database
- Display student photo
- Display student details
- Mark attendance automatically

7. Attendance Logic

If attendance already marked today:

- Show message:
  "Attendance already marked."

Otherwise:

- Save date and time
- Mark present

Late Attendance Logic:

- Before 8:00 AM → Present
- After 8:00 AM → Late

8. Student Verification Screen

After successful scan show:

- Student Photo
- Name
- Class
- Section
- Time
- Status

Display:
"Attendance Marked Successfully"

9. Reports Module

Generate:

- Daily attendance report
- Monthly attendance report
- Student-wise attendance report

Export:

- CSV
- Excel

10. Analytics Dashboard

Create graphs for:

- Daily attendance
- Monthly attendance
- Attendance percentage
- Late arrivals

Use Matplotlib.

11. Security Features

- Admin login screen
- Password protected dashboard
- Prevent duplicate attendance on same day

12. Future ESP32/Arduino Compatibility

Write code using modular architecture:

- scanner.py handles all scanning
- database.py handles all database operations

This should make it easy to replace the Python scanner with an ESP32 barcode scanner in the future.

